.
</p>

<p>
Thus, at Waterloo, Napoleon was compelled to wait till the ground became fi=
rm
enough for his guns to gallop over; nowadays every gun at his disposal, and
five times that number had he possessed them, might have opened on any poin=
t in
the British position he had selected, as soon as it became light enough to =
