n
degree. A theory which would leave any one of them out of account, or set u=
p
any arbitrary relation between them, would immediately become involved in s=
uch
a contradiction with the reality, that it might be regarded as destroyed at
once by that alone.
</p>

<p>
The problem is, therefore, that theory shall keep itself poised in a manner
