a step farther into the battle which is raging before us like a scene in a
theatre, we get to the nearest General of Division; here ball follows ball,=
 and
the noise of our own guns increases the confusion. From the General of Divi=
sion
to the Brigadier. He, a man of acknowledged bravery, keeps carefully behind=
