breast.
</p>

<p>
To add to all this, compassion strikes the beating heart with pity at the s=
ight
of the maimed and fallen. The young soldier cannot reach any of these diffe=
rent
strata of danger without feeling that the light of reason does not move her=
e in
the same medium, that it is not refracted in the same manner as in speculat=
ive
contemplation. Indeed, he must be a very extraordinary man who, under these
