that force upon any point Whatever of the theatre of War is such a use.
</p>

<p>
But if the maintenance of the troops in camp or quarters calls forth activi=
ties
which are no employment of the armed force, such as the construction of hut=
s,
pitching of tents, subsistence and sanitary services in camps or quarters, =
