such belong neither to strategy nor tactics.
</p>

<p>
Even entrenchments, the site and preparation of which are plainly part of t=
he
order of battle, therefore tactical subjects, do not belong to the theory o=
f
the conduct of War so far as respects the <i>execution of their constructio=
n</i> the
knowledge and skill required for such work being, in point of fact, qualiti=
