most matter-of-fact theories have, without knowing it, strayed over into th=
is
moral kingdom; for, as an example, the effects of a victory cannot in any w=
ay
be explained without taking into consideration the moral impressions. And
therefore the most of the subjects which we shall go through in this book a=
re
