alone can that effeminacy of feeling be counteracted, that propensity to se=
ek
for the enjoyment of comfort, which cause degeneracy in a people rising in
prosperity and immersed in an extremely busy commerce.
</p>

<p>
A Nation can hope to have a strong position in the political world only if =
its
character and practice in actual War mutually support each other in constan=
t
