in vain to calculate upon a surprise. But so general, indeed so indispensab=
le,
as is this endeavour, and true as it is that it is never wholly unproductiv=
e of
effect, still it is not the less true that it seldom succeeds to a <i>remar=
kable</i>
degree, and this follows from the nature of the idea itself. We should form=
