very severe loss on it by an unequal combat, provided that other circumstan=
ces
are in our favour. But such a scheme can never succeed except by a great
surprise, because no fractional part of the enemy=E2=80=99s Army would enga=
ge in
such an unequal combat, but would retire instead. But a surprise on an
