roads, and therefore during the march consider one division as forming the
reserve to the other. If an army in four divisions, of which three form the
front line and the fourth the reserve, is to march against the enemy in tha=
t
order, then it is natural to assign a road to each of the divisions in fron=
t,
and cause the reserve to follow the centre. If there are not three roads at=
