<h3><a name=3D"chap57"></a>CHAPTER XI.<br>Marches (<i>Continued</i>)</h3>

<p>
Respecting the length of a march and the time it requires, it is natural fo=
r us
to depend on the general results of experience.
</p>

<p>
For our modern armies it has long been settled that a march of three miles
should be the usual day=E2=80=99s work which, on long distances, may be set=
