elapse between the departure of the first and succeeding divisions.
</p>

<p>
We see, therefore, that the day is pretty well occupied with such a march; =
that
the fatigue endured by a soldier loaded with his pack for ten or twelve hou=
rs
is not to be judged of by that of an ordinary journey of three miles on foo=
t
which a person, on tolerable roads, might easily get over in five hours.
