</p>

<p>
In this all depends on time. The more time there is, the more general can t=
he
division be made, the less will it press on individuals, and the more regul=
ar
will be the result. Even purchases may be made with ready money to assist, =
in
which way it will approach the mode which follows next in order (Magazines)=
. In
all assemblages of troops in their own country there is no difficulty in
subsisting by regular requisitions; neither, as a rule, is there any in
