which we are not in possession, there is very little time for such
arrangements, seldom more than the one day which the advanced guard is in t=
he
habit of preceding the army. With the advanced guard the requisitions are s=
ent
to the local officials, specifying how many rations they are to have ready =
at
such and such places. As these can only be furnished from the immediate
