int,
the collections so made in haste will never be nearly sufficient for an arm=
y of
considerable strength, and consequently, if the troops do not carry with th=
em
enough for several days, they will run short. It is therefore the duty of t=
he
commissariat to economise what is received, and only to issue to those troo=
ps
who have nothing. With each succeeding day, however, the embarrassment
