of
stores, agents of administration, all these objects are constantly making u=
se
of these roads, and the total value of these services is of the utmost
importance to the army.
</p>

<p>
These great channels of life must therefore neither be permanently severed,=
 nor
must they be of too great length, or beset with difficulties, because there=
