</p>

<p>
The consequence is, that enterprises of this description on a flank, which =
have
always been more in fashion in books than in real warfare, now appear less =
of a
practical nature than ever, and we may safely say that there is no danger i=
n
this respect to any lines of communication but such as are very long, and
