partly on the division of nations formerly into small states, partly on the
periodical character of the incursions then in vogue, which had fixed and v=
ery
limited duration, almost in accordance with the seasons, as either the feud=
al
forces hastened home, or the pay for the condottieri used regularly to run
short. Since large standing armies, with powerful trains of artillery mow d=
own
the opposition of walls or ramparts as it were with a machine, neither town=
