Certainly, towns are not wanting which surpass others in size and importanc=
e,
as Nuremburg, Wurzburg, Ulm, Augsburg, and Munich; but if we are not dispos=
ed
to fortify all, there is no alternative but to make a selection. If, furthe=
r,
in accordance with our view, the fortification of the greatest and wealthie=
st
is held to be the principal thing, still it is not to be denied that, owing=
 to
the distance between Nuremburg and Munich, the first has a very different
strategic signification from the second; and therefore it always remains to=
