is equally strong everywhere. But such a camp can be <i>passed by</i>, and =
that
much easier than a fortified line, because its extent amounts to nothing.
</p>

<p>
Entrenched camps connected with fortresses are in reality of this second ki=
nd,
for the object of them is to protect the troops assembled in them; but thei=
