impassable nature (columns at that time not being able to quit the regular
roads), it was thought a wall of brass was thus presented to the enemy. As =
an
extra precaution, a few battalions, some horse artillery, and a dozen squad=
rons
of cavalry, formed a reserve to provide against the event of the line being
