this nothing was so favourable in general as mountainous ground. Thus it be=
came
an object to couple, as it were, the army with a formidable obstacle of gro=
und,
and the two united then made common cause. The battalion defended the mount=
ain,
and the mountain the battalion; so the passive defence through the aid of
