powerful element of strength; for one of the latter kind, on the contrary, =
it
is in general not at all suitable, or only so in some special cases.
</p>

<p>
In mountains every movement is slower and more difficult, costs also more t=
ime,
and more men as well, if within the sphere of danger. But the loss of the
assailant in time and men is the standard by which the defensive resistance=
