tion
to the whole body from which it is detached and in relation to the whole bo=
dy
of the enemy, the more this applies.
</p>

<p>
But a post also which is small in an absolute sense, that is, one which is =
not
opposed by an enemy superior to itself, and which, therefore, may aspire to=
