absolute defence, a real victory, will be infinitely better off in mountain=
s
than a large army, and can derive more advantage from the ground as we shal=
l
show further on.
</p>

<p>
Our conclusion, therefore, is, that a small post in mountains possesses gre=
at
strength. How this may be of decisive utility in all cases which depend
entirely on a <i>relative</i> defence is plain of itself; but will it be of=
