he
purpose. If we think only of the difficulty of covering absolutely a certai=
n
space, we should not believe this, but rather suppose, on the contrary, tha=
t it
must be very difficult for an army to protect its rear (that is, the countr=
y
behind it) against all expeditions which an enemy superior in numbers may
