condition of this constantly yielding, is always to continue formidable to =
the
enemy and not to allow him to beat us in detail, which might easily happen.=
 A
further object of such a retreat, is to bring our principal force by degree=
s to
a superiority of numbers, and with this superiority to give a decisive blow=
