s
fortresses and an arming of the people may be brought into use. In connecti=
on
with this it is advantageous if the flank of the principal theatre of war i=
s
fenced in by mountains, or otherwise very difficult tracts of country, whic=
h
stand forth as bastions, the strategic enfilade of which is to check the
