</p>

<p>
In the year 1800 it was not by the direct effect of the surprise, but by th=
e
false view which Melas took of the possible consequences of this surprise, =
that
his catastrophe was brought about.
</p>

<p>
Ulm, in the year 1805, was the last knot of a loose network of scientific b=
ut
extremely feeble strategic combinations, good enough to stop a Daun or a La=
scy
but not a Buonaparte, the Revolution=E2=80=99s Emperor.
</p>

<p>
The indecision and embarrassment of the Prussians in 1806, proceeded from
