<h3><a name=3D"chap96"></a>CHAPTER I.<br>The Attack in Relation to the Defe=
nce</h3>

<p>
If two ideas form an exact logical antithesis, that is to say if the one is=
 the
complement of the other, then, in fact, each one is implied in the other; a=
