preceding chapter we have shown that the power of the attack gradually exha=
usts
itself; possibly at the same time the superiority may increase, but in most
cases it diminishes. The assailant buys up prospective advantages which are=
 to
be turned to account hereafter in negotiations for peace; but, in the meant=
