t of
the attack, as already mentioned in the third chapter.
</p>

<p>
The only means of destroying the enemy=E2=80=99s armed force is by combat, =
but
this may be done in two ways: 1, directly, 2, indirectly, through a combina=
tion
of combats.=E2=80=94If, therefore, the battle is the chief means, still it =
is not
