is a loss of provinces to the defence, consequently of the sources of new
military forces.
</p>

<p>
4. That the advancing army gains a portion of those resources, in other wor=
ds,
gains the advantage of living at the expense of the enemy.
</p>

<p>
5. The loss of internal organisation and of the regular action of everythin=
g on
the side of the enemy.
</p>

<p>
6. That the allies of the enemy secede from him, and others join the conque=
ror.
